    14	        // Delta-encode a window's m/z slice. start/end are the first/last non-null m/z; values holds the
    15	        // consecutive deltas (length k-1 for a gapless slice) and excludes the start, which lives in start.
    16	        // Mirrors null_delta_encode: a value after a null is stored ABSOLUTE, a leading null is kept as a
    17	        // marker. The writer passes all-present slices, so this reduces to plain consecutive deltas.
    18	        public static void DeltaEncode(double?[] mz, out double start, out double end, out double?[] values)
